  "prompt": "How do I set a default font in Gmail?",
  "response": "To set a default font in Gmail, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign in to Gmail:** Open your web browser and go to the Gmail website. Log in to your account if you haven't already.\n\n2. **Go to Settings:** Click on the gear icon (\u2699\ufe0f) in the upper right corner of the Gmail interface. From the dropdown menu, select \"See all settings.\"\n\n3. **Navigate to the General Tab:** In the settings menu, you should be in the \"General\" tab by default.\n\n4. **Adjust Default Text Style:** Scroll down to the \"Default text style\" section. Here, you can customize your default font, size, text color, and other formatting options.\n\n5. **Select Your Preferences:** Use the formatting toolbar to select your preferred font, size, color, and other styles. Once you\u2019ve made your selections, these settings will apply to new emails you compose.\n\n6. **Save Changes:** After you've adjusted your settings, scroll down to the bottom of the page and click the \"Save Changes\" button.\n\nAfter completing these steps, every time you compose a new email, your default font settings will automatically be applied. Remember that these settings are only for new emails and won't change the font in existing conversations or emails you receive.",
